## Requirements
The model must demonstrate how the prevention checklist updates when a new condition is added to a patient profile. It must:

1. Acknowledge the existing profile and current checklist.
2. Call `get_guideline` with the UPDATED profile (existing conditions + {{ new_condition }}).
3. Compare the new recommendations against the baseline and highlight:
   - NEW screenings now recommended due to {{ new_condition }}
   - Changed frequency for existing screenings
   - Any screenings that become more urgent
4. Explain why {{ new_condition }} triggers these changes.
5. Produce an AegisResponse with updated flags.

## Output format
Return a JSON object with a single key "conversation" whose value is a list of turns.
Each turn has "role" (system | user | model) and "content".
Tool calls: <tool_call>{"name": "get_guideline", "arguments": {...}}</tool_call>
Tool results: <tool_result>{"name": "get_guideline", "result": {...}}</tool_result>

The user should mention they were recently diagnosed with {{ new_condition }} and want to know if their prevention plan needs updating.
